< review>
You always read reviews and hear stories about plumbing companies that are late to a job, never return calls, leave the job site a mess, and costs that require a second mortgage on the house.
Crystal Blue Plumbing and especially Brian (Plumbing Manager) Kylie, and Nathan are outstanding representatives of their company.  You want the best price, competent workers, professionalism, and responsiveness to your questions, call Crystal Blue Plumbing.

They recently repaired two main water service lines, for two adjoining properties, that had been damaged by the roots of a 70 foot Redwood Tree.  This involved 97 feet of trench across lawns with tons of tree roots.

Work was done in a timely manner, at a very reasonable price and the site was left as found.  Neat and clean.

Outstanding service from an excellent Company.  Give them a call.</review>

< review>
Crystal Blue replaced my furnace and A/C unit, and did a great job at a competitive rate. I was able to upgrade to a better unit than I had planned, because their rates were lower than the competitors.

However, dealing with their plumbing department is rough. We're supposed to have some kind of benefit from having our A/C +furnace replaced with them, but it's ill-defined and certainly not a benefit of timeliness or cost.

They came by once to diagnose a leak, and unplugged a drain, but root cause of the leak wasn't corrected. Later, I had a broken bathroom sink -- in our only bathroom -- and after finally arriving a week after my call, they quoted a price 3x the going rate in my zip code to install an identical replacement sink I bought at Home Depot.

I overheard the regular plumber and his manager, who tagged along, over my outside security camera talk the plumber's original price up and up. When I asked how they arrived at this $300/hr rate, the manager was non-specific and said it was to "cover their risk," and I ended up going with another local plumber who has market rates. I will not be taking advantage of their plumbing "benefit" ever again.</review>

I booked a virtual appointment for a general psych evaluation. I was hoping to get a second opinion on an ADHD diagnosis I had received from a different doctor. I called the office to explain that my co-pay should only be $30 and they let me know I would have to contact the financial department because they could not make that change. After a few weeks, they finally refunded me $220. After about a month, I randomly got another charge from Happier Living for $324.51. I called the office again to ask about this charge and they literally said, "I don't know what that charge is for." I had not had an appointment with them in over a month. I remember being overwhelmed because my medication dosages were being increased so fast. Because of my mental breakdown I went on Short term disability and paperwork had to be filed. I found the Genen Group after much research into decently reviewed mental health practitioners.  My experience has been generally pleasant, but the best interactions are with the incredible staff. Things to take into consideration

-traffic on the 101 is hit or miss. An emergency could easily add an hour to a 10 mile commute.
-there is no parking, which easily adds 10-20 minutes to your commute when you have to walk 1/2 mile.
-there is a 250 dollar late fee for being 10 minutes late to an appointment.

Unfortunately, this place would rather lose a customer than waive or lower the fees for being late the first time.

its not a matter of if you will get charged, its a matter of when.

Advice:
- for the sake of your mental health, do not go here

<Resp>None</Resp><review>I've been a patient since almost day one and have seen them grow from a one-man operation into a large office.  As a person with a disability, keeping track of my healthcare can be a full time job, and they do a great job making things as easy as possible for me.  Of the offices I visit, they are by far the most well-oiled machine.  Further, of all the LA mental health providers I've worked with, their office has been the best by far.

Pros:
- They're a one-stop-shop for your mental health needs.
- They take most insurance, which is rare for psychiatric care providers.
- They have a wide variety of professionals to fit the many needs of their patients.  Also, if you don't initially find the right match, you can switch to someone else in the office.
- They're always on-time.  Your appointment will start precisely on time every visit.  This is unlike any medical provider that I've ever had.
- Online patient data access with appointment reminders & everything else you could want.  Their online interaction is also VERY predictable, which can be a challenge for other offices.
- While not perfect, their billing department is probably the most straightforward of all my providers.  If things are off, they'll actually follow through to figure things out.
- The front desk staff is very helpful and friendly.
- Their location is within 'rolling' distance of my home.
- They are 100% wheelchair accessible.  There is an elevator in the building which has never been out of order.  Almost every hallway and doorway is wide enough to get around with ease.  Only one of their offices has two 29in doors and an uncomfortably narrow hallway, although it is still easily navigable for me.  Not all of their doorknobs are compliant, but there is a lobby on each floor so you can have your provider meet you there.  Their restrooms (which require a key and are common to the building) aren't fully compliant, but they're workable:  The entry door lacks ADA knobs, is just over 29in wide, and is a bit tough to open; but I've never required the assistance which they consistently offer.  Also, the stalls aren't full size, but have proper bars, etc.
Cons:
- Due to the number of professionals in their office, they have a somewhat larger turnover than most.  I've been assigned 4 different psychiatrists over the years, but the other member of my household has had the same one the entire time.  Of the 4, all but one was excellent, and the "less excellent" one didn't last very long.  On the psychology side, I've had two different therapists over the years during two different 'cycles' of therapy.  Both have been excellent.
- The various doctors can vary in quality.  But again, if one isn't a match, you still have other options.
- The fact that they're always on time means that YOU MUST ARRIVE ON TIME.  If you're at all late, you miss out on that part of your appointment.  This can be a difficult proposition in LA and even more so for someone with a disability like myself.  But, they will still let you see your doctor for an abbreviated session which means that you won't have to make due without your meds and assurance that your mental state hasn't deteriorated to critical levels.
- While some staff offer appointments into the evening, their office staff leaves at 5, and their phones stop ringing at 4.  For later appointments, they check you in 'automatically' which pretty much eliminates the problem.  These contact times are also in line with all of my medical providers.   The added convenience of later appointment options is really a plus, but keep in mind that you won't have anyone to deal with issues and check you in during these times.</review>< Pictures>

< text>
This is a comment, not about the doctors, but about the office practices. I still go to the Genen Group; however, I do have to agree with some of the reviews claiming that 1) no one answers the phone;  2) their preoccupation with money and fees; especially cancellation fees;  3) front office staff can be a bit "prickly" at times, especially as pertains to $$$$., 4) frequent (and in my opinion) unnecessary office visits. There also exists a double standard in regards to appointment cancellations. If a patient cancels without 24-hours notice, they are expected to pay a very hefty cancellation fee ($125 - keep in mind most doctors charge about $25). Yet, on several occasions I have been called at the last minute to reschedule or change appointment times because of issues on their end, yet I as a patient have no recourse.

My other pet peeve is that if you do cancel prior to 24 hours the only way you can avoid paying the fee is by submitting a doctor's note. When first told this, my reaction was "am I in grammar school?" They want a note from the doctor?  It felt condescending as I am an adult (a senior in fact) and felt I was being treated like a child. It would seem from their vantage point that the only type of reason accepted for a last-minute cancellation is patient illness, when in reality there are all sorts of reasons to cancel/reschedule an appointment.

I've been seeing psychiatrists for a long time (for medication checks only) and before going to the Genen Group it was never required of me to return on a monthly basis.  Most other psychiatrists expect a med-check every 6 months or so.  I questioned the doctor about this and commented that I wouldn't agree to monthly visits - similar to another review here, I've been on the same medication for years and don't need a monthly check-up. I was told that it is their policy, period. I am a bit stunned at their lack of flexibility as each patient is different and having a blanket policy just doesn't seem appropriate.

It would seem (since all of my "complaints" center around the theme of money) that what counts most is the bottom (profit) line. I know I can choose at any time not to go there and I hold that thought in the back of my mind; however the doctor I see is good and my well-being is more important to me than focusing on what might be considered sketchy office practices. It is a business after all.</text>

< Text>
I rarely if ever write reviews, but this group is outrageous. NOTHING "HAPPIER LIVING" about this group at all. One star is only because the MD and psychotherapist I had were actually good. Sure, office cancelled few of my appointments, sometimes pretty abruptly, sometimes causing me to go without meds for few weeks. But I didn't think too much of it as stuff happens. Last month one of the claims was denied and I called my insurance and Genen group right away to resolve it. Insurance needed med records due to Genen group apparently billing for a higher level of care (which sounds fishy), Genen group stated they sent all requested paperwork. No word from Genen Group after. Then on 11/13/17 I get an email stating they no longer take my insurance and all my appointments are cancelled starting 11/15/17. Would any responsible caring medical professional ever drop patients giving them 2 day notice? THAT is unprofessional at best. So I was already obviously upset because A) I had to find a new doctor and therapist, B) I had NO medications left, because their "standards" say that YOU HAVE TO come every 30 days for refills because obviously they want to bill more. The excuse that they provide to all patients here, that 30 day visits are needed because it's psychotropic meds or whatever it is they claim. I have been to other doctors, taken other medications, and NO ONE EVER thought every 30 days visit was required. I understand that with certain conditions, there is a need for frequent monitoring, dose adjustments, and so on. But not for the same medication, same dose, stable controlled condition. This practice puts patients in danger and is not done for safety. What if I got ill and missed my appointment? Then I should go without my meds until I see the MD? HALF OF PSYCH MEDS STATE: DO NOT STOP ABRUPTLY. Yet, Genen Group creates their own standard, where it is ok to stop anything whenever Genen group doesn't get reimbursed or has scheduling issue. With psych meds, I highly doubt it is the standard of practice to allow patients to skip weeks worth of medication because the provider cancels your appointments. In the best case scenario they could have at least provided a courtesy refill while I find a new MD. Now, last night, of course at the end of the day when you are unable to reach their office or your insurance, I get the email that Genen group is charging me 380$ in 4 days because I signed the agreement that if insurance doesn't pay, I am due for the full price of session. FINE, but isn't it at least human decency to provide more than 4 days heads up. Not everyone just has a spare 400$ sitting around. They could have notified me weeks ago when the claim was still denied. Yet, they never notified me of it. They waited long enough so they could charge the whole price. And from reviews below, I see that I am not the only one and sounds a lot like FRAUD. No self respecting company would do such a thing to people who are already under care due to medical issues. Never again would I recommend this horrible company to anyone else in my life, I will tell my MD to stop referring patients there because it is not how a human being should be treated. I just emailed them to let them know they HAVE to submit paperwork to my insurance. It is not even a matter of the money or payment, but how this company treats their patients. As a medical professional myself, I simply do not see how any self respecting and caring person can do this. I honestly hope that this group gets exposed for what they are doing. UNLESS YOU DON'T MIND PAYING HUGE AMOUNTS OF MONEY FOR QUICK VISITS EVERY SINGLE MONTH AND HAVING YOUR APPOINTMENTS CANCELLED WITH BARELY ANY NOTICE SOMETIMES, AND GETTING CHARGED MADE UP RATES FOR BEING LATE, MISSING YOUR APPOINTMENT, THEN THIS IS THE GROUP FOR YOU. OTHERWISE, BE AWARE THAT THEY WILL INCORRECTLY BILL YOUR INSURANCE, LEAVE YOU WITHOUT MEDICATION OR DOCTOR, AND SEND YOU A NICE BILL AS A PARTING GIFT.<//Text>

My wife was side swiped in a parking lot at the grocery store. We were recommended to Elite through Esurance, as they are one of the "star" repair shops. They fixed the car within a reasonable amount of time, as they did have to wait for some parts, but once the parts arrived, it was actually very quick. They had great customer service and were even fairly pro-active in getting us to pick up our car. Our work schedule around the holiday was a bit tough to work with. One note, they are not open on Saturday, even though the website and the sign on the front door say so. My first experience with Nir, I was recommended to him by the parts department guys @ the dealership I was at trying to get a replacement key for my car. The dealership wanted an outrageous amount and I needed all sorts of proof of ownership this and that, blah blah blah and even then I would have to wait for the key to be made and then shipped to me (2-3 business days). Sorry I just don't have the time for that! the car was registered in my dads name so imagine the hell I was going through just trying to get into my car. So I call Nir, he shows up within 1hr at most. immediately diagnoses my problem and lets me know ahead of time that I will most likely need the key to my car and a new steering column lock. he says its no problem, he gets to work, and by the end of the day, maybe 3-4 hrs max he has a new steering lock installed and has a brand new matching key, for believe it or not around 1/3 of what the dealership wanted. Not only that, he came to me so I didn't have to tow my car, and he had me back on the road with in hours. He is very professional and explains the situation very clearly so that you understand the work he is going to perform.

Fast forward a couple weeks, and my ECU burned up on my 01 Toyota 4runner. I replace the ECU but the car wont start, It just cranks. after some research I realize the car immobilizer doesn't recognize my car, and now I must reprogram the ECU to match my old key....So who do I call, once again Nir came to the rescue. This time he shows up in around 30 min. I am beyond please with me experiences so far with All American Lock and Key and especially with Nir.

< review>
Today I tried something different from El burrito. The carne asada burrito and it was just disgusting. I never had such nasty carne asada like I did today. The flavor was bad, the meat had a pink color to it and looked like undercooked hamburger meat.

I called the store and got a refund and told the girl about my order and was refunded immediately. So thank you for that. I am always weary of buying carne asada from Mexican places because only few make it how I like it. Which is browned and marinated and minced well, no chewy or fat peices. I recommend king taco in long beach or tortilla grill in Lancaster CA.

All in all I don't recommend this place, overpriced and low quality food. Try the more better locations such as Torrance Blvd or the one higher up on PCH.
Also don't get the carne asada, they don't use a high quality meat or marinade.

Thanks. But no thanks.</review>

So the positive is the place is fairly clean and they have a broad selection of breeds.

Sorry to say that‚Äôs where it ends.

First off when Patrick says his eggs are ‚Äúpastured‚Äù
And rotated daily it‚Äôs a complete lie. This place is on the side of a mountain no flat land.... no bigger then maybe at most 3 acres and 90% of it is for construction equipment storage ect. I‚Äôm sure that is what pays for his ‚Äúfarm‚Äù since it‚Äôs not his property but regardless. There are zero pastures, the pictures of birds on green grass are from a small backyard lawn behind their house. Also all of his products and so called organic feed is just Manna pro feed that he marks up as he‚Äôs a middle man and really doesn‚Äôt use quality feed like scratch and peck..

Sadly it gets worse. He will not stand behind his birds, products or own up to mistakes. He will hide
And make excuses for any problems that arise. Trust me If you want details message me!

Ultimately this place is basically a joke hobby for a guys who will not be in business 5 years from now.

Just beware< /review>

<response>None<//response>< text>
They were about to close but still had many people in. All the seats right now are separated with plastic shields, plenty available outside and inside. Their menu is different from what you see online - no tacos and only salmon/tuna/shrimp from the seafood options. No catch of the day neither. I had crab cakes-one of very few seafood options; and  hot chicken biscuit. Seemed like crab cakes is not a popular item - took awhile to arrive, actually the side dish it came with was amazing, crabcakes itself - okay, too mushy to my taste. Hot chicken biscut was great (came with fries). Biscuit was perfectly warm and slightly crunchy on the outside, but soft inside. Fried chicken was juicy and well seasoned - not too spicy though. Nice variety of drinks available - craft local beers, wines and selections of good quality spirits.</text>

OB Surf Lodge is "good enough." The service was good and the location was great; can't beat the ocean view. The food itself is good, just nothing worth getting excited about. I had the Carnitas Benny; which is eggs Benedict with Carnitas on top of what I think was an English muffin. The muffin was flat and a bit rough l, Soni couldn't really tell what it was. I had a mimosa flight. It came with 4 kinds of mimosa. They were decent enough, but you could taste the syrup. I'd come back if only for the atmosphere, but there are better brunch spots in OB.<//Text>

< Review>
This place is amazing. It looks awesome inside and out, the food is amazing, and it's all just... Cool as hell. I will be honest; the immediate, "Hello and welcome! Find any seat you'd like." with being handed a menu for my mother and I, felt good. Though the wait for the initial food and drink service did take some time, it is understandable given it is a slow morning. The waitress was kind and wasn't too energetic, which kinda went hand in hand with the theme of the place. I did feel bad though, because I was enjoying the entirety of the brunch menu, but I ultimately settled on the Smothered Omelette with apple juice. You can't go wrong with anything on the brunch menu, everything just sounds so good, and then when you get the actual plate, it's even better. 5/5 Will take family and friends here again.</Review>

<GmapID>0x80deaa3a4cd5c6e5:0x4a7106ced76f8d77< /GmapID>< Text>
My husband and I had our first date here when it was Shades in April 2007. We love the ocean view, the surfers, the dogs, and all the local color. It's our special place. The new management seems to have captured the essence of this sacred OB space - right on the water, next to the OB Pier, casual but elegant too. It's a bit pricier than it use to be - Bloody Mary's were $10 each, breakfast was $15 each, and a $50 dollar bill after we looked up from the waves. It didn't use to cost that! Nonetheless, we always go to this spot when we're visiting San Diego from the Palm Springs desert area. The OB Pier is our special spot. I just wish the new management had a drink special for us budget travelers. We shouldn't have to carry an AMEX card to go here.  This is OB man!<//Text>

< Text>
My husband and I had our first date here when it was Shades in April 2007. We love the ocean view, the surfers, the dogs, and all the local color. It's our special place. The new management seems to have captured the essence of this sacred OB space - right on the water, next to the OB Pier, casual but elegant too. It's a bit pricier than it use to be - Bloody Mary's were $10 each, breakfast was $15 each, and a $50 dollar bill after we looked up from the waves. It didn't use to cost that! Nonetheless, we always go to this spot when we're visiting San Diego from the Palm Springs desert area. The OB Pier is our special spot. I just wish the new management had a drink special for us budget travelers. We shouldn't have to carry an AMEX card to go here.  This is OB man!< /Text>

<user_id>102109112685024031364< /user_id>< Text>
My family and I went here today around noon to have lunch. The guy in the front said it would be about 15 minutes till we are seated. It took a bit longer but after reading the great reviews, we didnt mind. When we were finally seated around 12:40, the waitress took our drink order. The drinks came out quickly and we ordered shortly after. We noticed a couple who was seated prior to us still did not have their food and it was already 1. We waited almost an hour and still no food. Our waitress said the kitchen was backed up and said the food should come out soon. We saw a table of 5 near us get their food an hour later even though they were seated after us. The manager told my fiance they would push up our order. We waited over an hour for our waitress to then tell us our order would be placed in front. We ended up walking out after being there a total of 2 hours with no food. We wish we would have had a better experience but it seems like an hour wait for food is normal here. We had two kids with us and didnt want to keep waiting. My fiance used to work in the food business and said there is no reason to wait over an hour for food. I wouldnt go back after our experience.</Text>

<Time>1494995435974</Time><Rating>5< /Rating><Review>This place was a wonderful surprise!  Trying to find a somewhere  that cooked fresh cuisine (soy allergy)and could not have found a better meal! The chef came out and  reassured us its all freshly prepared. I had today's market fish which was the most delectable halibut in a white sauce served with roasted root veggies  (baby zucchini, small squash) and a pan seared swiss chard that was the best I've ever had. Hubby had the hanger steak (a flank steak marinated to such tenderness), garlic mashed and some vegetables (I didn't see or try those ).  The bill came to $48 and I even had a $6 drink.  Deal of the century!!  Full-on gourmet that would have cost twice as much anywhere else (we even ate outside staring at the ocean) to complete the top-notch dining experience!!  Will so be back next time in Ocean Beach!!!
